.TH "init_idle" 9 "init_idle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
init_idle \- set up an idle thread for a given CPU
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" init_idle
.BI "(struct task_struct *idle "  ","
.BI "int cpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "idle" 12
task in question
.IP "cpu" 12
CPU the idle task belongs to
.SH "NOTE"
this function does not set the idle thread's NEED_RESCHED
flag, to make booting more robust.
